    "created_at": "2015-09-23T14:21:20Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-23T14:21:20Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The the 'defaults' it falls back to are user configurable (there are hard-coded defaults which are updated from the the system wide `matplotlibrc` file and then the `~/.config/matplotlib/matplotlibrc`).  If at any point you had `interactive: true` in one of your default files it would have worked.  \n\nI think the consensus is that making interactive true by default is is a bad idea because it can mess wit using mpl in scripts.\n"
  },
